title: American support of the assassination of Iranian advisors
description: TEHRAN - In a conversation with Seyed Reza Sadr al-Hosseini, an expert on regional issues, the Iran newspaper discussed the Gaza war and America's support for the Zionist regime and wrote: The West Asia region is very important for Americans.

title: Safeguarding Islamic Revolution anchored in scientific advancements, President Raisi says
description: TEHRAN - President Ebrahim Raisi underscored on Tuesday the vital role of scientific and knowledge-based endeavors in ensuring the resilience of the Islamic Revolution.

title: Doha advocates dialogue as sole appropriate approach for addressing differences with Tehran
description: TEHRAN- The Qatari Foreign Ministry underscored Doha's consistent stance that the most suitable avenue for resolving differences with Iran is through diplomatic dialogue.

title: Iranians 'patient, pragmatic' to follow initiatives: Ex-Israeli official
description: TEHRAN- According to a former chief of Israel’s military intelligence, Iran is “pragmatic” and has “patience” in spades to carry out its objectives in the West Asia region, including the annihilation of Israel.

title: Sobh Intl. Media Festival to shine spotlight on Palestinian cause
description: TEHRAN-The upcoming Sobh International Media Festival will dedicate a special section to the Palestinian cause, the organizers have announced.

title: list of Assembly of Experts’ candidates to be unveiled on Wednesday
description: TEHRAN - The Ministry of Interior is set to unveil the list of qualified candidates for the upcoming Assembly of Experts election on Wednesday.

title: Israel turns to criminal acts out of desperation: spokesman
description: TEHRAN – Iranian government spokesman Ali Bahadori Jahromi says the assassination of Iranian military advisors in Syria by Israel indicated the regime’s desperate acts due to its continued failures.

title: Iran Army incorporates new home-grown drones
description: TEHRAN – In a momentous development, new home-grown drones, meticulously crafted through collaboration between the Iranian Ministry of Defense and the Iranian Army, have been officially incorporated into the Armed units at multiple sites across the nation.

title: Yemen’s actions in Red Sea are independent: IRGC
description: TEHRAN – The commander of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps Navy has affirmed the independent actions of Yemeni armed forces in their military operations in the Red Sea.

title: “Hospital Is Not a War Zone” cartoon exhibit opens in Tehran
description: TEHRAN-A cartoon and caricature exhibition dedicated to the theme of Israeli forces bombing hospitals in Gaza was opened during a ceremony at Tehran’s Art Bureau on Monday.

title: Raisi to arrive in Turkey on Wednesday
description: TEHRAN- On Wednesday, Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi will pay an official visit to Turkey to talk about measures to strengthen ties.

title: IRGC offers satellite launch services to neighboring nations
description: TEHRAN- The Commander of the IRGC Aerospace Force's Space Division has stated that it is prepared to launch satellites for neighboring countries, provided that the government can facilitate the necessary negotiations.

title: Iran warns UK, U.S. attacks on Yemen aim to give Israel more room to kill people
description: TEHRAN – Iran’s foreign ministry spokesman on Tuesday slammed the latest round of American and British attacks on Yemeni soils, saying the airstrikes do nothing to ensure maritime security in the Red Sea.

title: Why was Mohammad Ghobadloo put to death?
description: TEHRAN – A 23-year-old man was hanged on Tuesday after being found guilty of killing one police officer and injuring five others during the unrest that shook Iran in September 2022.

title: Iran calls Israel 'helpless' in war, attacking Syria, Lebanon to offset 'disgraceful' loss to Gaza
description: TEHRAN- Israel’s latest strikes on Syria and Lebanon, according to Iran’s Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian, are an attempt to deflect attention away from the regime’s “disgraceful defeat” in the Gaza conflict.

title: ‘Agree on something you can do: Cutting off the Zionist regime’s lifeline’
description: TEHRAN- In a meeting with the organizers of the National Congress for the Commemoration of the 24,000 Martyrs from Tehran, the Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei, criticized the officials of Islamic countries for their poor conduct regarding the highly crucial situation in Gaza.

title: Iran storm to 2023 AFC Asian Cup knockout stage with perfect record
description: TEHRAN – Iran national football team defeated the UAE 2-1 and advanced to the 2023 AFC Asian Cup knockout stage as Group C winners.

title: Hamas elaborates on the October 7 operation
description: TEHRAN- The Palestinian resistance group Hamas has published an 18-page report outlining the reasons why it carried out its military operation on October 7?, and what happened on that day.

title: West Azarbaijan invests $130 million in tourism projects
description: TEHRAN – In a bid to boost tourism infrastructure, Iran’s West Azarbaijan province has allocated an investment of 65 trillion rials (some $130 million) for the execution of 50 tourism projects, the provincial tourism chief said on Tuesday.

title: Mazandaran province maps out visionary tourism plan
description: TEHRAN – The northern Mazandaran province, which is bounded by the Caspian Sea and the towering Alborz range, is in the process of formulating a comprehensive tourism plan.

title: FITUR highlights: Iran’s pavilion set to wow spectators with traditional performances
description: TEHRAN - Visitors to Iran’s pavilion at the International Tourism Fair FITUR in Spain will be treated to a captivating display of traditional performances this year.

title: Do we have to go to Mars to see the Martian Mountains?
description: TEHRAN – In fact, you don’t have to go to Mars to experience the breathtaking beauty of the Martian Mountains! Instead, you may plan a trip to explore a similar mesmerizing destination in southeast Iran!

title: IRCS to strengthen cooperation with Libya, Tajikistan
description: TEHRAN –The Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) has announced readiness to enhance ties with the Red Crescent societies of Libya and Tajikistan.

title: Iran, Pakistan to further expand scientific ties: official
description: TEHRAN – The main challenges in the development of Islamabad–Tehran relations have been overcome and the two countries are ready to further boost ties in higher education, science, and technology, the chairman of Pakistan's higher education commission has said.

title: Iran ready to assist Cuba for ICT growth
description: TEHRAN – Iranian companies are ready to enter the Cuban market and transfer their experiences in the field of information and communications technology, ICT minister Issa Zarepour has said.

title: TEDPIX loses 26,500 points on Tuesday
description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), lost 26,527 points (1.24 percent) to 2,120,035 on Tuesday, which is the fourth day of Iranian calendar week.

title: Iron ore pellet production up 10% in 9 months on year
description: TEHRAN- Production of iron ore pellet in Iran rose by 10 percent during the first nine months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21-December 21, 2023), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, according to the data released by the Iranian Steel Producers Association (ISPA).

title: Tochal ski resort
description:
Tochal is one of the most famous ski resorts in Iran. Located in northern Tehran, the site can be reached via a four-mile journey by cable car that leaves from the northern suburbs of Tehran.   

At 3963m, Tochal ski resort is the fifth-highest resort in the world, ensuring a long season from December to at least April and sometimes June.

The resort hosts two restaurants and a hotel with 26 rooms and four suites.

title: Persepolis complete signing of Issa Alekasir
description: TEHRAN – Issa Alekasir became second January signing of Persepolis football club.

title: Tanzania inks agreement to pay its debts to Iran
description: TEHRAN- Based on an agreement signed between Tanzania and Iran, the African country will pay its debts to Iran, an official with Organization for Investment, Economic and Technical Assistance of Iran announced on Monday.

title: ‘Expert consensus in solving economic challenges is least expensive path’
description: TEHRAN- The deputy head of Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA) said the expert consensus in solving economic challenges is the least expensive path.

title: 19th Tehran Auction to present classic, modern Iranian art
description: TEHRAN-The 19th edition of the Tehran Auction with a collection of classic and modern Iranian art will be held on January 26 at Parsian Azadi Hotel in Tehran.

title: Iran sixth at 2024 Asian Handball Championship
description: TEHRAN – Iran were edged by South Korea 27-26 at the 2024 Asian Handball Championship on Monday to come in sixth place.

title: Iran's exports to China rise 30% in December 2023
description: TEHRAN – The value of Iran’s exports to China increased by 30 percent in December 2023 as compared to the same month in 2022, according to China’s Customs data.

title: What is Islamic tile?
description: Islamic tile is an important art form in the history of Islamic art. Islamic artists and artisans developed it over centuries as a branch of architecture and interior decoration. Islamic tiles can be found in many countries, but Iran is particularly well-known for its tile industry. This industry is divided into pre-Islamic and post-Islamic periods, with the beginning of tile-making in Iran dating back to the Sassanid era.

title: Aziznia becomes first Iranian to conquer Vinson Massif
description: TEHRAN - Elite Iranian climber Andrew Aziz (Amin Aziznia) has achieved a remarkable feat by becoming the first Iranian man to climb Vinson Massif, the highest peak in Antarctica, which stands at 4,892 meters (16,050 feet).

title: Commodities worth over $731m traded at IME in a week
description: TEHRAN- During the past Iranian calendar week (ended on Friday), Iran Mercantile Exchange (IME) witnessed trade of 3,908,033 tons of commodities with a total trading value of more than $731 million on its physical market.

title: 24 Israeli troops, 21 in a single incident, killed in Gaza in one day
description: Israeli army spokesperson Daniel Hagari provided more details on the two dozen troops killed on Monday– the deadliest since the Gaza ground incursion began, Al Jazeera reported.
